item.description:
In this example, we want to sync example.com except &lsquo;example.com/temp_uploads&rsquo;
rsync -avz --exclude 'example.com/temp_uploads' example.com /var/www_backups  NOTE:
 exclude files are always relative to current directory. to exclude multiple directories, just use an additional &lsquo;&ndash;exclude&rsquo; statement.  details in https://www.thegeekstuff.com/2011/01/rsync-exclude-files-and-folders
